    <div class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-[.2em] text-gold mt-8">Location</div>
    <p class="mt-8">The JJK Gurukulam is located in Thiruvananthapuram, at Vattiyoorkavu, a serene and picturesque area surrounded by coconut trees. Thiruvananthapuram (Trivandrum) is an ancient city with a rich history dating back to 1000 BC. It became the capital of the Kingdom of Travancore in 1750. The name “Thiruvananthapuram” is derived from the words Thiru-Anantha-Puram, meaning “the city of Anantha” or “the abode of the sacred serpent Anantha” upon whom Lord Vishnu, the preserver in the Hindu Trinity, reclines.</p>
    <p>Thiruvananthapuram, the capital city of Kerala, is situated on the southwestern coast of India near the southern tip of the mainland. It is a beautiful seaside city built across seven hills. One of its most iconic landmarks is the Sri Padmanabhaswamy Temple, a magnificent temple believed to be nearly 2000 years old.</p>
